      • stage

        public Software.StageInvocation stage(java.lang.String host,
                                      SoftwareTypes.StageSpec spec)
        Description copied from interface: Software
        Stages the desired software document associated with the given host. If getCommit() property is Set, it implies the minimum commit that the Software.stage(java.lang.String, com.vmware.esx.settings.hosts.SoftwareTypes.StageSpec) method should use, however if subsequent commits have been made to the desired state document the stage method will use the most recent desired state document. The result of this operation can be queried by calling the cis/tasks/{task-id} where the task-id is the response of this operation. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:

      • check

        public Software.CheckInvocation check(java.lang.String host,
                                      SoftwareTypes.CheckSpec spec)
        Description copied from interface: Software
        Runs checks on the host before applying the desired software document. Checks if host is in a good state to be updated with the desired software document. If getCommit() property is Set it implies the minimum commit that the check method should use, however if subsequent commits have been made to the desired state document the check method will use the most recent desired state document. The result of this operation can be queried by calling the cis/tasks/{task-id} where the task-id is the response of this operation. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        The results of all checks performed.

        Specified by:
        check in interface Software
        Parameters:
        host - Identifier of the host. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: HostSystem.
        spec - Check specification.
        Returns:
        instance of Software.CheckInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described check operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
